18:20.640 --> 18:22.640
- Hello.
- Elliot, dance with me first.

18:22.720 --> 18:25.000
- No, Elliot, dance with me.
- He's dancing with me first.

18:25.080 --> 18:26.160
You can dance with me.

18:26.160 --> 18:28.760
That's enough. Break
it up. He belongs to me.

18:28.840 --> 18:30.120
Hey, Elliot, how the hell are you?

18:30.120 --> 18:31.680
Somebody take a picture
of me and Elliot.

18:31.760 --> 18:34.160
- Hold it.
- Excellent.

18:34.200 --> 18:37.920
- Hi, Elliot.
- Ooh.

18:39.720 --> 18:42.000
I think she likes you too.

18:42.040 --> 18:44.760
- <i>You hungry?</i>
- Sort of.

18:44.800 --> 18:45.080
Look.

18:45.080 --> 18:48.280
Wow. These look just like the
cookies my grandma used to bake.

18:48.360 --> 18:51.240
- Try one.
- Okay.

18:51.320 --> 18:53.840
These are the cookies
my grandma used to bake!

18:53.840 --> 18:55.360
I aim to please, handsome.

18:55.440 --> 18:58.000
- Come on.
- How did you...

18:59.280 --> 19:01.920
- You liked that, didn't you?
- What, the cookie?

19:01.960 --> 19:05.560
Having all those people
excited to see you.

19:05.600 --> 19:07.640
It's nice to feel
accepted, isn't it?

19:07.720 --> 19:09.600
I can give you that.

19:09.680 --> 19:12.480
I can make the
whole world love you.

19:12.520 --> 19:14.680
- Come on.
- <i>You still don't believe me.</i>

19:14.720 --> 19:17.280
- Do you?
- Of course not.

19:17.360 --> 19:20.720
first of all,
you look nothing like the Devil.

19:20.800 --> 19:24.000
Oh, really? I suppose
I could have gone this way.

19:26.360 --> 19:29.320
But it's so "trick or treat."

19:29.400 --> 19:32.960
It's true.
You really are the Devil.

19:33.040 --> 19:36.320
Oh. Come on, baby.
Come and sit down.

19:36.400 --> 19:39.680
I know this has all been
horribly overwhelming for you.

19:39.720 --> 19:42.440
- Can I ask you a question?
- Sure you can.

19:42.520 --> 19:43.800
You can ask me anything you like,

19:43.800 --> 19:45.560
as long as you don't
ask me if there's a God.

19:45.600 --> 19:49.360
I get that one all the time.
It drives me absolutely bonkers.

19:50.720 --> 19:52.600
<i>Yes, there's a God.</i>

19:52.640 --> 19:55.200
Really?
Well, what's He like?

19:55.280 --> 19:58.560
You know, you'd think that meeting
the Devil would be interesting enough,

19:58.640 --> 20:01.080
but no, all people
want to know about is Him.

20:01.120 --> 20:03.000
Like He's so bloody fascinating.

20:03.040 --> 20:06.040
- So, He's a man?
- Yeah. Most men think they're God.

20:06.080 --> 20:07.960
This one just happens
to be right.

20:08.000 --> 20:09.880
<i>Now listen, darling.</i>

20:09.920 --> 20:11.440
I don't wanna pressure you,

20:11.440 --> 20:14.600
but why don't we take a teensy
little look at the contract?

20:20.960 --> 20:24.840
This is pretty... Um...

20:24.920 --> 20:29.160
"I, Elliot Richards,
hereafter known as the Damned..."

20:29.240 --> 20:32.120
- "The Damned"?
- How about "the Darned"? Sound better?

20:32.160 --> 20:34.440
Don't get hung up on
the language, darling.

20:34.440 --> 20:35.920
There's nothing sinister here.

20:36.000 --> 20:38.440
It's all standard boilerplate.

20:38.520 --> 20:43.640
Paragraph one states that I, the Devil,
a not-for-profit cooperation...

20:43.680 --> 20:45.520
with offices in Purgatory,
Hell and Los Angeles,

20:45.520 --> 20:46.560
will give you seven wishes...

20:46.600 --> 20:48.960
to use as you see fit.

20:49.000 --> 20:51.200
Seven?
Why not eight?

20:51.280 --> 20:54.760
Why not six? I don't know.
Seven just sounds right.

20:54.840 --> 20:56.880
Paragraph two outlines
the manner in which you'll pay

20:56.880 --> 20:57.960
for the aforementioned wishes.

20:58.040 --> 20:59.920
What? Are you kidding?

20:59.920 --> 21:01.280
I have to give you my soul?

21:01.360 --> 21:04.240
After you've had
your wishes, of course.

21:04.240 --> 21:05.600
But it's my soul!

21:05.640 --> 21:09.200
- I can't give you my soul!
- What are you, James Brown?

21:09.280 --> 21:11.800
What's the big deal?
Have you ever seen your soul?

21:11.880 --> 21:13.760
<i>Do you even know what it is?</i>

21:13.760 --> 21:15.840
Of course.
It's the thing that... that...

21:17.040 --> 21:19.000
No, that's the...
It floats around...

21:19.080 --> 21:21.280
Can I tell you something?

21:21.360 --> 21:23.760
Souls are overrated.

21:23.840 --> 21:27.440
They don't really do anything.
Has yours done anything for you so far?

21:27.520 --> 21:31.400
No. It's like your appendix.
You'll never even miss it.

21:31.480 --> 21:34.560
Yeah, well, if it's so useless,
then how come you want it so much?

21:34.640 --> 21:36.960
Ooh, aren't you the clever one?

21:37.000 --> 21:40.640
Look, who's really making out
on this deal here?

21:40.720 --> 21:45.320
Seven utterly fabulous wishes
for one piddling little soul?

21:45.400 --> 21:47.240
Well, I don't know.

21:47.320 --> 21:49.480
What have we here?

21:54.360 --> 21:57.280
But who is that? Alison?

21:58.720 --> 22:00.680
How did you...

22:00.760 --> 22:03.280
She is so beautiful.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.840
- I've been waiting for you for so long.
- Who's that?

22:07.880 --> 22:10.920
- Who's she with?
- I want you now, my love.

22:11.000 --> 22:13.600
- Why are you showing me this?
- I'm yours forever, my darling.

22:13.680 --> 22:16.600
Oh, I love your hair like that.

22:16.640 --> 22:19.480
You must go through
conditioner like crazy.

22:20.720 --> 22:23.680
- Is this real?
- It could be.

22:23.760 --> 22:25.960
All you have
to do is sign.

22:26.040 --> 22:27.320
And you promise I'll get her?

22:27.320 --> 22:29.880
It's really up to you.
You're the one with the wishes.

22:29.960 --> 22:34.080
But I promise
I'll do everything in my power.

22:34.160 --> 22:36.000
Sign it, Elliot.

22:45.000 --> 22:48.960
Please, Elliot. I'm waiting.

23:12.320 --> 23:14.440
- Great!

23:14.520 --> 23:17.640
Now, before you start wishing,
you'll be needing this.

23:17.720 --> 23:20.600
If for any reason your wish
isn't going the way you hoped,

23:20.640 --> 23:23.640
just take out the pager,
hit 666...

23:23.680 --> 23:25.920
and it'll bring you
right back to me.

23:25.960 --> 23:29.600
Why wouldn't it go
the way that I'd hoped?

23:29.640 --> 23:32.160
Oh, I was just throwing
that out as a "for instance."

23:32.240 --> 23:35.520
Every wish is gonna be
100% fabulous.

23:35.600 --> 23:39.160
But you'll find that out
as soon as you make one.

23:39.240 --> 23:41.400
So, I should make one now?

23:41.440 --> 23:44.880
Well, if you don't mind.
I've got places to go,

23:44.960 --> 23:48.160
people to condemn
to an eternity of fiery torment.

23:48.200 --> 23:51.360
Okay. Um, let me think.

23:51.440 --> 23:54.560
- I wanna be married to Alison.
- You got it.

23:54.600 --> 23:57.040
Um, that's not all.
I wanna be rich.

23:57.120 --> 23:59.960
- Always a popular choice.
- That's not all.

24:00.000 --> 24:03.960
I wanna be very rich
and very powerful.

24:04.040 --> 24:07.520
Oh, even better.
Remember, you have to say "I wish."

24:07.600 --> 24:09.480
Right.

24:09.560 --> 24:12.520
I wish that I were married
to Alison...

24:12.600 --> 24:15.160
and that I were very, very rich
and very powerful.

24:15.240 --> 24:17.840
- How's that sound?
- Sounds good to me.

24:17.920 --> 24:20.400
Enjoy.

