25:55.760 --> 25:57.400
Que diablos!

27:22.240 --> 27:24.440
- <i>Bueno.</i>
- Roberto.

27:29.680 --> 27:31.200
<i>Si.</i>

28:29.200 --> 28:33.560
<i>Corazon. Corazon!</i>

28:49.760 --> 28:53.480
I am is to visiting
in the Los <i>Angeles...</i>

28:53.520 --> 28:56.960
for the time of vacations.

29:37.960 --> 29:40.440
<i>Idiota!</i>

29:43.720 --> 29:46.120
<i>Jefe.</i>

30:43.400 --> 30:45.440
<i>Corazon.</i>

32:10.760 --> 32:12.840
<i>Es cocaina!</i>

33:37.480 --> 33:39.680
<i>Alejandro?</i>

33:39.720 --> 33:43.480
<i>Alejandro? Roberto? Esteban?</i>

35:02.760 --> 35:05.200
<i>Seis, seis, seis.</i>

35:10.680 --> 35:13.960
Back so soon?

35:20.040 --> 35:23.960
You turned me into a drug dealer.
They almost killed me.

35:24.040 --> 35:27.080
- You asked for rich and powerful.
- Not like that.

35:27.160 --> 35:31.520
Goes with the territory, babe.
Root of all evil. Ring any bells?

35:31.560 --> 35:35.680
- What about Alison? What got into her?
- I think it was Raoul.

35:35.720 --> 35:38.160
Yeah! That's not
what I wished for.

35:38.240 --> 35:39.640
Well, hold on now, mister.

35:39.640 --> 35:42.000
You wished that the
two of you were married.

35:42.080 --> 35:44.800
You didn't say anything
about her loving you.

35:44.840 --> 35:47.560
Well, you know, when two people
get married, I assume that...

35:47.640 --> 35:51.480
There's your mistake.
May I suggest something?

35:51.560 --> 35:51.800
What?

35:51.800 --> 35:54.720
The rich and powerful thing
wasn't really the way to go.

35:54.760 --> 35:57.920
Everyone wishes for that first thing
out of the gate and it never pans out.

35:57.960 --> 36:00.000
- Really?
- The fact of the matter is...

36:00.040 --> 36:03.360
women aren't really attracted
to wealth and power.

36:03.400 --> 36:05.760
- They're not?
- No, of course not.

36:05.800 --> 36:08.200
They couldn't give a fig
for all that rubbish.

36:08.280 --> 36:11.240
What you need to figure out
is what she does want in a man.

36:11.320 --> 36:13.160
How do I find that out?

36:13.240 --> 36:14.560
Easy.

36:14.560 --> 36:15.240
Easy.

36:23.320 --> 36:25.560
I'm not with her!

36:28.840 --> 36:29.640
<i>Where are we?</i>

36:29.640 --> 36:32.120
<i>A place you never would</i>
<i>have seen without my help.</i>

36:32.160 --> 36:34.160
<i>Welcome to Alison's bedroom.</i>

36:34.720 --> 36:38.120
We can't be in here. This
is breaking and entering.

36:38.200 --> 36:40.040
I know.
It's fun, isn't it?

36:40.120 --> 36:43.680
I'm sure we're gonna find the
answer somewhere around here.

36:43.760 --> 36:46.600
- What if Alison catches us?
- <i>Don't worry.</i>

36:46.680 --> 36:48.520
She won't be able to see you.

36:48.600 --> 36:52.560
- Besides, she's in the shower... naked.
- 

36:52.600 --> 36:56.080
<i>Right behind that door.</i>
<i>Go on. Go ahead. Take a peep.</i>

36:56.160 --> 36:59.480
- No!
- Oh, come on. We both know you want to.

36:59.560 --> 37:01.720
You must think that
I'm really perverted, don't you?

37:01.760 --> 37:02.800
That's what you think.

37:02.800 --> 37:05.480
You think I'm some sad,
desperate, twisted, pathetic loser.

37:05.560 --> 37:05.800
Yes.

37:05.800 --> 37:09.240
Well, in that case, maybe
I'll just take a quick look.

37:09.280 --> 37:13.480
<i>Focus, Elliot. Remember, we're here</i>
<i>to find out what kind of man she wants.</i>

37:13.560 --> 37:16.920
- How are we gonna do that?
- Well, she keeps a journal.

37:17.000 --> 37:20.160
Aha. And here it is.

37:20.240 --> 37:23.000
Right. I should be able to find some
information in here you'll find useful.

37:23.080 --> 37:26.600
- Hey, that's private stuff.
- Is it ever. Listen to this.

37:26.680 --> 37:29.720
"Last night was the most
incredible night of my life.

37:29.800 --> 37:33.640
<i>"I never did find out any of the guys'</i>
<i>names, but I brought them back here...</i>

37:33.720 --> 37:36.600
and all five of them banged me
like a Salvation Army drum."

37:36.680 --> 37:37.080
What?

37:37.080 --> 37:40.400
Just kidding. I could
have been a writer.

37:45.920 --> 37:50.000
<i>Hey, it's okay. She could bump</i>
<i>into you and she wouldn't feel it.</i>

37:50.040 --> 37:52.440
Now, this is good.

37:52.480 --> 37:54.840
"I meet many attractive men

37:54.880 --> 37:56.080
who are interested in me,

37:56.120 --> 37:59.960
"and while many of them are handsome
or clever or very successful,

38:00.040 --> 38:02.840
<i>"I find myself turning away</i>
<i>from them...</i>

38:02.880 --> 38:07.240
"and searching the horizon
for someone else.

38:07.320 --> 38:09.600
"I don't know who he is
or where I'll find him.

38:09.680 --> 38:13.920
"I only know that
he is a sensitive man.

38:14.000 --> 38:17.040
"He's a man who is in touch
with his emotions.

38:17.080 --> 38:20.320
"He's a man who's not afraid
to share his fears,

38:20.400 --> 38:22.800
"his disappointments
and his tears.

38:22.840 --> 38:25.240
<i>Where are you,</i>
<i>my sensitive man?"</i>

38:34.560 --> 38:37.360
Did you see that?

38:37.400 --> 38:41.240
She passed right through me.
We were one person for a split second,

38:41.320 --> 38:43.480
just like in <i>Ghost.</i>

38:43.560 --> 38:45.920
Darling, I've got an earthquake
in Chile in eight minutes.

38:45.920 --> 38:47.160
Any chance of making a wish here?

38:47.200 --> 38:50.480
Yes. I wish...

38:50.520 --> 38:52.880
I were the most
sensitive man in the world.

38:52.920 --> 38:54.840
Right. Okay.

38:54.920 --> 38:59.760
Wait! I wish I were the most
emotionally sensitive man in the world.

38:59.840 --> 39:01.960
Damn. I was hoping you
wouldn't catch that.

39:01.960 --> 39:04.040
I could have had a lot
of fun with that one.

39:04.120 --> 39:07.480
- And I want her to love me.
- Oh. You know what?

39:07.560 --> 39:09.720
I have a great feeling
about this.

39:09.800 --> 39:13.000
- You do?
- Yeah, but... what do I know, right?

39:24.240 --> 39:26.680
- Hey.
- I'm back, my love.

39:26.760 --> 39:27.960
Where did you run off to?

39:27.960 --> 39:29.920
I went to make a
garland of beach plums...

39:30.000 --> 39:32.880
to place atop your glorious head
like a crown.

39:34.360 --> 39:37.360
But then I caught sight
of that sunset and...

39:37.400 --> 39:40.120
I don't know, something
stirred inside me...

39:40.200 --> 39:43.320
and I had to stop and weep.

39:43.360 --> 39:46.760
<i>Mmm, it's beautiful.</i>

39:46.840 --> 39:48.680
It is.

39:51.280 --> 39:53.400
- There I go again.
- Tissue?

39:53.440 --> 39:56.320
No, I never wipe
my tears away.

39:56.400 --> 39:59.480
I'm not ashamed of them.
I wear them proudly,

39:59.560 --> 40:03.080
like small, wet, salty
badges of emotional truth.

40:03.160 --> 40:07.160
Elliot, um, there's something that
I think that we should talk about.

40:07.240 --> 40:11.960
Um, we've been together for
what, about three weeks now?

40:12.040 --> 40:15.120
- Three magical weeks.
- Three magical weeks.

40:15.160 --> 40:19.560
And I don't think that I've ever
met a man who's been more in touch...

40:19.640 --> 40:23.360
- with his feelings.
- I love you... so very much.

40:23.440 --> 40:25.560
I love you too.

40:28.640 --> 40:31.800
Dudley! Peter!

40:33.280 --> 40:35.160
I'm sorry.
They're such little devils.

40:35.200 --> 40:37.400
Come on, you naughty boys.
See ya.

40:40.000 --> 40:42.200
I'm sorry.
Are you okay?

40:42.240 --> 40:45.320
Um, do you need comforting
on any level?

40:45.400 --> 40:47.240
No, no, no, I'm fine.

40:47.320 --> 40:51.320
Have I done or said anything to
make you feel less good about you?

40:51.400 --> 40:54.320
- No, no, no, I'm fine.
- Would you like something to eat?

40:54.400 --> 40:58.840
I made a salad nicoise
with dolphin-safe tuna.

40:59.880 --> 41:02.200
Oh, wow.

41:07.080 --> 41:10.240
- What is it?
- It's that sunset again.

41:10.320 --> 41:13.800
And I worry about the dolphins.
I wrote a song about them.

41:13.800 --> 41:15.200
Would you like to hear it?

41:15.280 --> 41:18.040
Now? l-l...

41:20.280 --> 41:23.280
# Mayo-nayo-naise ##

41:26.240 --> 41:31.480
# Swimming by the sandy shore
Dancing up among the waves #

41:31.560 --> 41:34.240
# Dolphin, dolphin I adore #

41:34.320 --> 41:36.720
# Everything you are #

41:36.760 --> 41:39.560
#You're so much more
than a fish to me #

41:39.640 --> 41:42.400
# My playful friend
beneath the sea ##

41:45.760 --> 41:48.520
- I have to stop.
- Good! I mean, oh, why?

41:48.600 --> 41:51.480
Because I'm looking at you
and I'm seeing all the beauty...

41:51.560 --> 41:54.600
of the world shining at me
through your eyes.

41:54.680 --> 41:58.000
- Would you mind if I sketched you?
- I didn't know you could draw.

41:58.080 --> 42:00.200
I'm not an artist, per se.

42:00.280 --> 42:03.040
Okay, Elliot, there's something
that I think I really have to say.

42:05.960 --> 42:07.800
Elliot, that's amazing!

42:09.240 --> 42:11.120
Compared to you, it's nothing.

42:11.200 --> 42:13.560
Compared to your smile...

42:13.600 --> 42:16.320
<i>and the blush of your cheek and</i>
<i>the sound of your voice as it</i>

42:16.320 --> 42:17.520
<i>floats on the evening breeze.</i>

42:17.600 --> 42:21.160
Compared to you,
that sunset's just...

42:24.480 --> 42:26.880
When is that darn thing gonna set?

42:26.960 --> 42:28.800
- Maybe we should go.
- No, wait.

42:28.880 --> 42:33.280
There's so much that I wanna say to you,
but I just can't find the words.

42:33.360 --> 42:35.760
I have an idea.
I would like...

42:35.840 --> 42:38.800
to improvise a sonnet
about your hair.

42:40.800 --> 42:43.720
How wonderful
my fair one's face...

42:48.480 --> 42:50.960
Excuse me, fellas.
Might I ask you to...

42:51.040 --> 42:53.880
take the horseplay down
to another part of the beach?

42:53.920 --> 42:56.280
Uh, no.

43:00.800 --> 43:05.000
<i>You know, rather</i>
<i>than get confrontational,</i>

43:05.080 --> 43:07.040
why don't we all
just sit down together,

43:07.120 --> 43:12.320
have some salad with dolphin-safe tuna
and see if we can't start a dialogue.

43:13.520 --> 43:16.000
You know, I had a feeling
that you were gonna...

43:16.080 --> 43:20.120
Okay, guys, I'm afraid
I'm going to have to ask you...

43:20.160 --> 43:23.680
to respect the moment that
my woman friend and I are sharing...

43:23.760 --> 43:27.480
because it's a special celebration
of love and caring...

43:27.520 --> 43:31.280
and a unique spiritual
and emotional understanding.

43:33.120 --> 43:35.720
- You wanna get a beer?
- Sure.

43:35.800 --> 43:38.680
Alison, excuse me, but I thought
that this was our time together.

43:38.760 --> 43:40.640
It's just a beer.
I'll be back in two seconds.

43:40.720 --> 43:42.880
Actually, my place
is like 40 minutes from here.

43:42.960 --> 43:45.520
- That's fine. Which way is your car?
- It's a van.

43:45.600 --> 43:46.040
Great.

43:46.040 --> 43:50.040
Alison, I respect your
uniqueness and individuality.

43:50.120 --> 43:53.720
And you're your own person, and if you
want to go with our new friends here...

43:53.760 --> 43:55.920
to get a drink,
I won't stand in your way.

43:56.000 --> 43:58.080
Okay, thanks, El.
I knew you'd understand.

43:58.080 --> 43:58.640
No, wait!

43:58.720 --> 44:00.920
Don't go! I can't handle
this kind of rejection!

44:00.920 --> 44:02.600
Why don't you wanna
stay here with me?

44:02.680 --> 44:06.280
You wanna know why?
Because you're just too sensitive!

44:06.360 --> 44:09.200
I'm about to go out of my mind here.
It's been wonderful,

44:09.280 --> 44:12.520
and God knows I love you,
but enough is enough!

44:12.600 --> 44:16.680
I just wanna be with a man who will
ignore me and take me for granted...

44:16.760 --> 44:19.000
and who's only pretending
to be interested in who I am...

44:19.040 --> 44:21.840
and what I think so
he can get into my pants.

44:21.920 --> 44:25.800
- That would be me.
- Oh, thank you!

44:25.880 --> 44:28.080
Let's get out of here.

44:28.160 --> 44:30.040
Alison, wait!

44:30.120 --> 44:32.600
<i>Alison!</i>

